  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether eradication of Helicobacter pylori
      infection is effective in the improvement of platelet counts in children and adolescents with
      chronic ITP.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Helicobacter pylori infection has been associated with Immune Thrombocytopenic Purpura (ITP),
      and there is scientific evidence for the investigation and treatment of this bacterium for
      adult patients with ITP. However, in children this causal association is not clear, with few
      published studies.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
